2019-12-18 13:48:06	FromGitter	<watzon> I like YAML personally. It's concise and supports a lot of things that JSON doesn't, like multiline strings for instance
2019-12-18 13:48:24	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> same
2019-12-18 13:50:01	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> I like yaml for the right use cases
2019-12-18 13:50:09	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> big k8s manifests really stretch that
2019-12-18 13:50:50	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> and it's a superset so you're not constrained
2019-12-18 13:51:12	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> although yaml has some weirdness, like 'null' values
2019-12-18 13:51:32	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> saw your messages about PHP earlier @Blacksmoke16
2019-12-18 13:51:37	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> the weirdest part of PHP has to be https://www.php.net/manual/en/language.variables.variable.php
2019-12-18 13:52:53	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> @tenebrousedge I wasn't trying to do anything, I just discovered go's `buildmode=plugin` and I was thinking about this kind of thing before as a way of extending Crystal apps without recompiling the world
2019-12-18 13:52:59	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> just curious
2019-12-18 13:53:33	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> haven't written any Crystal or been active here in forever, just want a reason to write some Crystal :[
2019-12-18 13:54:01	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> @Blacksmoke16 I'm a fan of code configuration if it's appropriate
2019-12-18 13:54:44	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> like, if you're configuring the app, why not utilise the app to configure itself
2019-12-18 13:55:44	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> or laravel uses config PHP files, etc.
2019-12-18 13:56:28	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> But then on the flip side, I think something like Wordpress shouldn't use `wp-config.php`, but should use yaml
2019-12-18 13:56:40	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> or just be incinerated altogether
2019-12-18 13:58:04	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> yea for sure
2019-12-18 13:58:16	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> main usage would be for like CORs
2019-12-18 13:58:48	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> or like global app settings, like `logs_dir`, default charset etc
2019-12-18 13:59:10	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> if you're doing for a framework, then in-app
2019-12-18 13:59:11	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> eventually want to get to the point where you define parameters, then use the parameters in the config as well
2019-12-18 13:59:20	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> if it's a binary that you just consume, then yaml
2019-12-18 13:59:54	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> hmm good point
2019-12-18 14:00:05	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> it would be kinda annoying to have to ship your binary with a yaml file...
2019-12-18 14:01:03	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> just dump out a default one or use defaults and make it optional
2019-12-18 14:01:27	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> at that point whats the point of having the file?
2019-12-18 14:01:42	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> well you ship it with sane defaults
2019-12-18 14:01:45	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> and let people override
2019-12-18 14:02:32	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> i guess what im trying to get at is, is it bad to have to ship a yaml file with your binary
2019-12-18 14:02:46	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> that controls those overridden settings
2019-12-18 14:03:03	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> vs having that in the binary and it configures itself
2019-12-18 14:03:12	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> based on ENV vars or what have you
2019-12-18 14:04:26	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> it depends whether your app is something highly reusable or if it's going to be configured at build
2019-12-18 14:05:03	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> like, if it's your business app that gets deployed with highly specific business config, I'd say you manage it in-app/talk to services like consul
2019-12-18 14:05:16	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> use case would be for athena ofc
2019-12-18 14:05:38	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> which i cant imagine people changing the settings once its running
2019-12-18 14:05:39	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> or if it's something highly generic like hugo, consul, etc. that you configure with the CLI, env, etc. then I'd say config file(s)
2019-12-18 14:05:48	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> Yeah, I'd say in-app
2019-12-18 14:06:07	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> that makes things a lot easier as well...
2019-12-18 14:06:21	FromGitter	<Blacksmoke16> still going to make a PR for custom yaml tags, think that would be cool :P
2019-12-18 14:06:34	FromGitter	<absolutejam_gitlab> like our production Laravel app, we have 20+ config files that all call out to env (and in prod we use Consul-template), and eventhough you can change things on the fly, we ship it as a docker image so it's essentially a 'binary'
